'[Verse 1]\n[A]I was buried beneath my [D]shame\n[A]Who could carry that kind of [E]weight\n[A]It was my tomb till I [D]met You\n[A]You called my name and I [E]ran out\n[F#m]And I don''t know why a [D]King would choose\nTo [A]run to [E]me\n\n[Chorus]\n[D]O what a glorious [A]day\n[D]What a glorious way that You have [E]saved me\n[D]O what a glorious [A]name\n[D]What a glorious name it is [E]Jesus [A]',
'A', 0, 76, '4/4', 'Verse1, Chorus', 1, TRUE),

(43, 'Give Me Faith', 'Elevation Worship', 'Brown Bannister, Chris Brown, Mack Brock, Wade Joye', 'english',
